# ./ "root the op of the file system  hierarchy"
/bin Binaries and other executables programs.
/etc system configuration files
/ home home directories
/opt Optional or third party softwars
/ tmp Temporary space,
/usr User related programs
/var var data, most notably log files

BASIC COMMANDS
ls = List directory content
cd = change the current
pwd Display the present working directory
cat=concatnatd 
echo=display 
man= disokay the online manual
giz -h compress or uncompress files

. This directory
.. the parent directory
cd - change to the previous directory 

/ directory forward slash
mkdir[-p] - create a directory
rmdir [-p] - remove a directory
rm -rf directory -recursively removes directory
ls -F to reveal file type
